When I tried to use DPI-C, I faced this bug report:
> verilator -cc --Mdir ./build/obj_dir --top-module TOP /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/ErythrinaCore.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/extern_modules.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/MemManager.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/TOP.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/IFU.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/MEMU.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/halter.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/IDU.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/EXU.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/WBU.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/RegFile.sv /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/ALU.sv
                    ... Known scopes under 'halt': <no instances found>
%Error: Internal Error: /home/yzcc/ysyx-workbench/npc/build/halter.sv:8:10: ../V3LinkDot.cpp:2731: Couldn't resolve inlined scope 'erythrinacore' in: TOP.erythrinacore.IDU_inst.HaltCtrl
    8 |          halt();
While in `halter.sv` I have:
```
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.62.0
module halter(
   input   wire halt_trigger
);
   import "DPI-C" function void halt();
   always @(*) begin
      if (halt_trigger) begin
         halt();
      end
   end
endmodule
```
